726167f-a.title: Queens: Borden Avenue - 5th Street
726167f-a.text:
Borden Avenue, north side, east from 5th Street. On the
corner is the yard of the Arthur Johnson Corporation, con-
trastors, the other buildings being old tenements. On the left
is the spire of St. Mary's Roman Catholic Church and on the ex-
treme right the Vernon Boulevard viaduct..
P. L. Sperr  October 25, 1936

726168f-a.title: Queens: Borden Avenue - 5th Street
726168f-a.text:
Borden Avenue, at the N.W. corner of 5th Street, showing
the Long Island Railroad branch of the Y.M.C.A. Across the
roof of the building are the stacks of the Pennsylvania Rail-
1road power house.
P. L. Sperr  October 25, 1936

726169f-b.title: Queens: Borden Avenue - 5th Street
726169f-b.text:
Borden Avenue, west from 5th Street, toward the East River.
The first building on the right is the Long Island Railroad
branch of the Y.M.C.A. On the south side of the avenue (left)
are the yards of the Long Asland Railroad. The Empire State
Building appears in views 1 and 3.
P. L. Sperr  October 25, 1936
NO REPRODUCTIONS  Views 1,2,3
